<div id="review_2779616391" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2779616391" />
    <a title="Mandy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/37976064-mandy"><img alt="Mandy" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2779616391?book_show_action=true">Apr 08, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mandy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mandy" href="/user/show/37976064-mandy">Mandy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2779616391" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7014375007960538195">This is a great devotional for the busy person - and who isn&apos;t a busy person? These are short but solid bits of goodness to help you refocus back on the Lord and off of the crazy distractions of the world. I like that these are not dated, so you can pick whichever devotion is speaking to you that day. There is also an index by topic, such as doubt, faith, loneliness, etc., and also by Scripture reference. I have the Kindle version, so I love that I can just go to the topical index, find what I&apos;m</span>
  <span id="freeText7014375007960538195" style="display:none">This is a great devotional for the busy person - and who isn't a busy person? These are short but solid bits of goodness to help you refocus back on the Lord and off of the crazy distractions of the world. I like that these are not dated, so you can pick whichever devotion is speaking to you that day. There is also an index by topic, such as doubt, faith, loneliness, etc., and also by Scripture reference. I have the Kindle version, so I love that I can just go to the topical index, find what I'm dealing with that day, click on the link and be taken straight to that devotional. Do yourself a favor and read this book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7014375007960538195" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
